{"id":653371772,"lang":"cpp","lang_name":"C++","time":"1 year, 6 months","timestamp":1646420444,"status":10,"status_display":"Accepted","runtime":"12 ms","url":"/submissions/detail/653371772/","is_pending":"Not Pending","title":"Palindrome Number","memory":"5.9 MB","code":"class Solution {\npublic:\n    bool isPalindrome(int x) {\n        \n        \n        if(x < 0 || (x % 10 == 0 && x != 0)) {\n            return false;\n        }\n\n        int revertedNumber = 0;\n        while(x > revertedNumber) {\n            revertedNumber = revertedNumber * 10 + x % 10;\n            x /= 10;\n        }\n\n        // When the length is an odd number, we can get rid of the middle digit by revertedNumber/10\n        // For example when the input is 12321, at the end of the while loop we get x = 12, revertedNumber = 123,\n        // since the middle digit doesn't matter in palidrome(it will always equal to itself), we can simply get rid of it.\n        return x == revertedNumber || x == revertedNumber/10;\n    }\n};","compare_result":"","title_slug":"palindrome-number","has_notes":false,"flag_type":1}
